{{see|Plough}}
==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* {{US}} [[plow]]
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[plōh]]''
===Noun===
'''plough'''  (pl. ''ploughs'')

# A device pulled through the ground in order to break it open into [[furrow]]s for planting.
#:''The horse-drawn plough had a tremendous impact on agriculture.''

====Translations====
